- "voyages" are the orders they embarked upon; 
- "treasures" represent the total value of items in each order, 
- "chests" symbolize the merchants offering the items, 
- "weight of their gold" is a metaphor for the total order value, 
- "ranked by the weight of their gold" refers to the ranking of orders based on their total value; 
- "from the heaviest to the lightest" means the highest to the lowest total value; 
- "value of treasures" refers to the total value of the items in each order.
